## Specification Reference
- **Primary**: INV-FERR-013 (Checkpoint Equivalence), spec/02 §23.2
- **Primary**: INV-FERR-028 (Cold Start Latency), spec/03 §23.3
- **Primary**: INV-FERR-076 (Positional Content Addressing), spec/09 §23.8.5
- **Supporting**: ADR-FERR-010 (Two-Tier Type System — WireDatom trust boundary)

## Performance Context
| Scale | V2+OrdMap | V3 deserialize |
|-------|----------|---------------|
| 200K | 89s | ~20ms |
| 100M | ~52hr | ~10s |

## Resolved Type Decisions
1. Two-struct serialization pattern matching V2 (ADR-FERR-010):
   - V3PayloadWrite: uses Vec<Datom> (Datom has Serialize only)
   - V3PayloadRead: uses Vec<WireDatom> (WireDatom has Deserialize), then .into_trusted()
2. Fixed header + single bincode call for payload (Option C). Zero cursor arithmetic.
3. Schema pairs SORTED by attribute name before serialization (deterministic output).
4. bitvec crate must have serde feature enabled for BitVec Serialize/Deserialize.
5. V2 detection by magic "CHKP" vs "CHK3" in deserialize_checkpoint_bytes.

## Pseudocode — Types (in checkpoint/v3.rs)

```rust
use serde::{Serialize, Deserialize};
use bitvec::prelude::{BitVec, Lsb0};
use ferratom::{AgentId, AttributeDef, Datom, FerraError};
use ferratom::wire::{WireDatom, WireCheckpointPayload};

const V3_MAGIC: [u8; 4] = *b"CHK3";
const V3_VERSION: u16 = 3;
const V3_HEADER_SIZE: usize = 4 + 2 + 8 + 16; // magic(4) + version(2) + epoch(8) + genesis(16)
const HASH_SIZE: usize = 32;

/// V3 serialization payload. Uses Datom (has Serialize, NOT Deserialize).
/// ADR-FERR-010: write path uses core types directly.
#[derive(Serialize)]
struct V3PayloadWrite {
    schema_pairs: Vec<(String, AttributeDef)>,
    datoms: Vec<Datom>,
    live_bits: BitVec<u64, Lsb0>,
}

/// V3 deserialization payload. Uses WireDatom (has Deserialize).
/// ADR-FERR-010: read path uses wire types, then into_trusted().
#[derive(Deserialize)]
struct V3PayloadRead {
    schema_pairs: Vec<(String, AttributeDef)>,
    datoms: Vec<WireDatom>,
    live_bits: BitVec<u64, Lsb0>,
}
```

## Pseudocode — serialize_v3_bytes

```rust
pub(crate) fn serialize_v3_bytes(store: &Store) -> Result<Vec<u8>, FerraError> {
    let mut buf = Vec::new();
    // Fixed header
    buf.extend_from_slice(&V3_MAGIC);
    buf.extend_from_slice(&V3_VERSION.to_le_bytes());
    buf.extend_from_slice(&store.epoch().to_le_bytes());
    buf.extend_from_slice(store.genesis_agent().as_bytes());

    // Collect datoms from whichever variant (DatomIter yields &Datom)
    let datoms: Vec<Datom> = store.datoms().cloned().collect();

    // Extract or rebuild live_bits
    let live_bits: BitVec<u64, Lsb0> = match &store.repr {
        StoreRepr::Positional(p) => p.live_bits_clone(),
        StoreRepr::OrdMap { .. } => {
            // Rebuild: datoms are EAVT-sorted (DatomIter from OrdSet iterates in Ord order)
            crate::positional::build_live_bitvector_pub(&datoms)
        }
    };

    // Schema pairs sorted by name for deterministic output (INV-FERR-013)
    let mut schema_pairs: Vec<(String, AttributeDef)> = store.schema().iter()
        .map(|(a, d)| (a.as_str().to_owned(), d.clone()))
        .collect();
    schema_pairs.sort_by(|(a, _), (b, _)| a.cmp(b));

    // Single bincode payload — one call, zero cursor arithmetic
    let payload = V3PayloadWrite { schema_pairs, datoms, live_bits };
    let payload_bytes = bincode::serialize(&payload)
        .map_err(|e| FerraError::CheckpointWrite(e.to_string()))?;
    buf.extend_from_slice(&payload_bytes);

    // BLAKE3 over all preceding bytes
    let hash = blake3::hash(&buf);
    buf.extend_from_slice(hash.as_bytes());
    Ok(buf)
}
```

## Pseudocode — deserialize_v3_bytes

```rust
pub(crate) fn deserialize_v3_bytes(data: &[u8]) -> Result<Store, FerraError> {
    // Size check
    if data.len() < V3_HEADER_SIZE + HASH_SIZE {
        return Err(FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: format!("at least {} bytes for V3 checkpoint", V3_HEADER_SIZE + HASH_SIZE),
            actual: format!("{} bytes", data.len()),
        });
    }

    // BLAKE3 verify
    let (content, hash_bytes) = data.split_at(data.len() - HASH_SIZE);
    let computed = blake3::hash(content);
    if computed.as_bytes() != hash_bytes {
        return Err(FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: "valid BLAKE3 checksum".to_string(),
            actual: "checksum mismatch".to_string(),
        });
    }

    // Parse fixed header (magic already checked by dispatcher)
    let epoch = u64::from_le_bytes(
        content[6..14].try_into().map_err(|_| FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: "8-byte epoch at offset 6".to_string(),
            actual: "truncated header".to_string(),
        })?
    );
    let genesis_bytes: [u8; 16] = content[14..30].try_into().map_err(|_|
        FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: "16-byte genesis_agent at offset 14".to_string(),
            actual: "truncated header".to_string(),
        }
    )?;
    let genesis_agent = AgentId::from_bytes(genesis_bytes);

    // Single bincode deserialize — ADR-FERR-010: uses WireDatom
    let payload: V3PayloadRead = bincode::deserialize(&content[V3_HEADER_SIZE..])
        .map_err(|e| FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: "valid V3 bincode payload".to_string(),
            actual: e.to_string(),
        })?;

    // Validate live_bits length
    if payload.live_bits.len() != payload.datoms.len() {
        return Err(FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
            expected: format!("live_bits.len() == datoms.len() ({})", payload.datoms.len()),
            actual: format!("live_bits.len() = {}", payload.live_bits.len()),
        });
    }

    // Trust boundary crossing: WireDatom → Datom (ADR-FERR-010)
    // BLAKE3 verified above, so into_trusted() is appropriate
    let datoms: Vec<Datom> = payload.datoms.into_iter()
        .map(|wd| wd.into_trusted())
        .collect();

    // Build schema
    let mut schema = ferratom::Schema::empty();
    for (name, def) in payload.schema_pairs {
        schema.define(ferratom::Attribute::from(name.as_str()), def);
    }

    // Build PositionalStore directly — datoms already EAVT-sorted, live_bits provided
    // pub(crate) field construction — same crate
    let positional = PositionalStore {
        canonical: datoms,
        live_bits: payload.live_bits,
        perm_aevt: OnceLock::new(),  // lazy (bd-vhmc)
        perm_vaet: OnceLock::new(),
        perm_avet: OnceLock::new(),
        fingerprint: [0u8; 32],      // recomputed by bd-83j4 when landed
    };
    let positional = Arc::new(positional);

    // Build live_causal/live_set from the trusted datoms
