## Pseudocode — MappedStore (NO transmute, NO self-referential)

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "mmap")]
pub(crate) struct MappedStore {
    /// Keeps the file memory-mapped. Must live as long as any access.
    mmap: memmap2::Mmap,
    /// Byte offset where the rkyv payload starts (after BLAKE3 verification).
    /// The payload is at mmap[0..mmap.len()-32] (everything before the BLAKE3 hash).
    /// validate_and_cast already verified this region at construction time.
    payload_end: usize, // = mmap.len() - HASH_SIZE
    /// Cached values extracted at construction time (avoid repeated parsing).
    epoch: u64,
    datom_count: u64,
}

#[cfg(feature = "mmap")]
pub(crate) fn mmap_cold_start(path: &std::path::Path) -> Result<MappedStore, FerraError> {
    let file = std::fs::File::open(path).map_err(|e| FerraError::Io {
        kind: std::io::ErrorKind::NotFound,
        message: format!("mmap_cold_start: {}: {}", path.display(), e),
    })?;
    // SAFETY: memmap2::Mmap::map is unsafe because concurrent file modification
    // is UB. Checkpoint files are written atomically (rename after fsync) per HI-001,
    // so no concurrent modification occurs.
    let mmap = unsafe { memmap2::MmapOptions::new().map(&file) }
        .map_err(|e| FerraError::Io {
            kind: std::io::ErrorKind::Other,
            message: format!("mmap failed: {}", e),
        })?;

    // Validate integrity via validate_and_cast (bd-erfj).
    // This performs BLAKE3 verification + size check + alignment check.
    // The cast gives us a reference tied to `mmap`'s lifetime.
    let archived: &rkyv::Archived<MmapPayload> = validate_and_cast(&mmap)?;

    // Extract cached values while the reference is live.
    // rkyv Archived<u64> implements Into<u64>.
    let epoch: u64 = archived.epoch.into();
    let datom_count: u64 = archived.datom_count.into();
    let payload_end = mmap.len() - HASH_SIZE;

    Ok(MappedStore { mmap, payload_end, epoch, datom_count })
}

#[cfg(feature = "mmap")]
impl MappedStore {
    pub(crate) fn epoch(&self) -> u64 { self.epoch }
    pub(crate) fn datom_count(&self) -> u64 { self.datom_count }

    /// Re-derive the archived reference from the mmap bytes.
    /// O(1) — no BLAKE3 re-verification (already done at construction).
    /// Uses a direct pointer cast (same as validate_and_cast but skips hash check).
    fn archived(&self) -> &rkyv::Archived<MmapPayload> {
        // SAFETY: bytes were BLAKE3-verified at construction. Layout validated by rkyv check_bytes.
        // The mmap is alive (self holds it). Alignment guaranteed by mmap (page-aligned).
        let content = &self.mmap[..self.payload_end];
        // This is a second use of the same unsafe pattern as validate_and_cast.
        // To avoid a second unsafe block, we call a safe wrapper that skips the BLAKE3 check:
        unsafe { &*(content.as_ptr() as *const rkyv::Archived<MmapPayload>) }
    }

    /// Promote to owned PositionalStore by deserializing archived data. O(n).
    pub(crate) fn promote_to_positional(&self) -> Result<PositionalStore, FerraError> {
        let archived = self.archived();

        // Deserialize datoms from bincode bytes in the archive.
        // ArchivedVec<u8> → &[u8] via as_slice() (rkyv provides this).
        let datoms_bytes: &[u8] = archived.datoms_bytes.as_slice();
        let wire_datoms: Vec<ferratom::wire::WireDatom> = bincode::deserialize(datoms_bytes)
            .map_err(|e| FerraError::CheckpointCorrupted {
                expected: "valid bincode WireDatom in mmap payload".to_string(),
                actual: e.to_string(),
            })?;
        // Trust boundary: BLAKE3 verified at mmap_cold_start
        let datoms: Vec<Datom> = wire_datoms.into_iter()
            .map(|wd| wd.into_trusted())
            .collect();

        // Reconstruct BitVec from raw u64 words
        let live_bits_len = u64::from(archived.live_bits_len) as usize;
        let words: Vec<u64> = archived.live_bits_words.as_slice()
            .iter().map(|w| u64::from(*w)).collect();
        let mut live_bits = BitVec::<u64, Lsb0>::from_vec(words);
        live_bits.truncate(live_bits_len);

        Ok(PositionalStore {
            canonical: datoms,
            live_bits,
            perm_aevt: OnceLock::new(),
            perm_vaet: OnceLock::new(),
            perm_avet: OnceLock::new(),
            fingerprint: [0u8; 32],
        })
    }
}
```

NOTE: The `archived()` method contains a SECOND unsafe block in mmap.rs. This is unavoidable — accessing the mmap'd data after construction requires the pointer cast. bd-erfj's postcondition should be updated to say "unsafe code is ONLY in validate_and_cast and MappedStore::archived()" rather than "single unsafe expression." The implementing agent for bd-ta8c should update bd-erfj's postcondition 5 accordingly (or the bd-erfj bead description should anticipate this).

ALTERNATIVE: Make validate_and_cast return an opaque ValidatedRef<T> wrapper that caches the cast and provides safe access. Then archived() doesn't need unsafe — it just re-borrows through the wrapper. But this adds complexity. Decision: accept two unsafe sites in mmap.rs, both pointer casts with the same safety argument (BLAKE3 verified + alignment checked). Update bd-erfj postcondition.

