## Resolved Type Decisions
1. Use std::sync::OnceLock (stable since Rust 1.70, in std — no external dependency)
2. OnceLock<Vec<u32>> does NOT implement Clone. PositionalStore must impl Clone manually: clone initialized OnceLock values, leave uninitialized ones as OnceLock::new()
3. from_datoms() builds canonical + live_bits ONLY. Permutations are OnceLock::new()
4. build_permutation() helper is UNCHANGED — called from get_or_init closures
5. merge_positional() result has uninitialized perms (same as from_datoms)
6. Arc<PositionalStore> in StoreRepr means the OnceLock init is shared across all Arc clones — init once, visible to all readers. OnceLock is Sync, so concurrent get_or_init is safe.

