## Performance Context
MMPH: O(1) entity→position lookup. Constant time regardless of scale. EntityId (BLAKE3, 32 bytes, uniform) is ideal input — no clustering, no pathological patterns.

| Scale | Interpolation search (bd-u6bq) | MMPH | Space overhead |
|-------|-------------------------------|------|----------------|
| 200K | ~20ns | ~30ns (hash + verify) | ~75KB |
| 100M | ~400ns | ~35ns | ~37.5MB |

MMPH is most valuable at 10M+ where interpolation still has several DRAM misses. At small scale, interpolation is faster (no hash overhead).

## Resolved Type Decisions
1. OnceLock<Option<Mph>> — lazy init on first entity_lookup(). None = build failure → binary search fallback.
2. Mph struct in mph.rs wraps implementation. Interface is SPECIFIED. Implementation is the ONE constrained agent choice: safe Rust MPH crate (<1 year maintained, MIT/Apache, no internal unsafe) OR inline CHD (<200 LOC) OR BinarySearchFallback (deferred).
3. entity_lookup: MPH gives position in UNIQUE ENTITY array. Map to canonical position via first_datom_position_for_entity (partition_point). O(1) existence via MPH + O(log n) position lookup. For absent entities: MPH returns arbitrary position → verify-after-lookup catches mismatch.
4. Reuses unique_entity_ids() from bd-218b (or introduces it if bd-218b not yet landed).
5. Mph stores the sorted unique EntityId Vec for verify-after-lookup.

## Pseudocode — mph.rs (NEW ~100 lines)

```rust
//! Monotone Minimal Perfect Hash for entity lookups (bd-wa5p, INV-FERR-076).

use ferratom::EntityId;

/// MPH over EntityIds. O(1) lookup for present keys.
/// For absent keys: returns arbitrary position — caller MUST verify.
#[derive(Clone)]
pub(crate) struct Mph {
    /// Sorted unique EntityIds (for verify-after-lookup).
    keys: Vec<EntityId>,
    /// Implementation — agent chooses one:
    inner: MphInner,
}

#[derive(Clone)]
enum MphInner {
    /// Always-correct O(log n) fallback. Used if no safe MPH crate available.
    BinarySearchFallback,
    // Future: Chd(ChdTable), CrateWrapper(ExternalMph)
}

impl std::fmt::Debug for Mph {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "Mph(keys={}, impl=", self.keys.len())?;
        match &self.inner {
            MphInner::BinarySearchFallback => write!(f, "BinarySearchFallback"),
        }?;
        write!(f, ")")
    }
}

impl Mph {
    /// Build from sorted unique EntityIds. Returns None on failure.
    /// Agent: search crates.io for safe MPH crate. If none found, use BinarySearchFallback.
    pub(crate) fn build(sorted_keys: Vec<EntityId>) -> Option<Self> {
        Some(Self { keys: sorted_keys, inner: MphInner::BinarySearchFallback })
    }

    /// O(1) lookup for the unique-entity-array index.
    /// For BinarySearchFallback: O(log n) binary search.
    /// Caller MUST verify keys[result] == query_key.
    pub(crate) fn lookup(&self, key: &EntityId) -> Option<usize> {
        match &self.inner {
            MphInner::BinarySearchFallback => self.keys.binary_search(key).ok(),
        }
    }

    /// Verify that a lookup result matches the query key.
    pub(crate) fn verify(&self, idx: usize, key: &EntityId) -> bool {
        self.keys.get(idx).is_some_and(|k| k == key)
    }
}
```

## Pseudocode — PositionalStore integration (positional.rs)

```rust
use crate::mph::Mph;

// Add field to PositionalStore:
mph: OnceLock<Option<Mph>>,

// In manual Clone impl (bd-vhmc pattern):
mph: match self.mph.get() {
    Some(opt) => { let l = OnceLock::new(); let _ = l.set(opt.clone()); l }
    None => OnceLock::new(),
},

// In from_datoms:
mph: OnceLock::new(),  // lazy

impl PositionalStore {
    /// O(1) entity → canonical position lookup via MPH (INV-FERR-027).
    ///
    /// Returns the canonical position of the FIRST datom for this entity.
    /// Returns None if entity is not in the store.
    #[must_use]
    pub fn entity_lookup(&self, eid: &EntityId) -> Option<u32> {
        let mph_opt = self.mph.get_or_init(|| {
            Mph::build(self.unique_entity_ids())
        });

        // Fast path: MPH tells us if the entity EXISTS in O(1).
        // Then find the canonical position via partition_point.
        if let Some(mph) = mph_opt {
            if let Some(idx) = mph.lookup(eid) {
                if mph.verify(idx, eid) {
                    // Entity confirmed present. Find first datom position.
                    return self.first_datom_position_for_entity(eid);
                }
            }
            // MPH miss or verify failed → entity absent
            return None;
        }

        // Fallback: binary search
        self.first_datom_position_for_entity(eid)
    }

    /// Find canonical position of first datom for entity. O(log n) via partition_point.
    fn first_datom_position_for_entity(&self, eid: &EntityId) -> Option<u32> {
        let pos = self.canonical.partition_point(|d| d.entity() < *eid);
        if pos < self.canonical.len() && self.canonical[pos].entity() == *eid {
            u32::try_from(pos).ok()
        } else {
            None
        }
    }
}
```

